    takeaways: [ "Occasional forgetting is a normal part of aging; dementia is not.", "Normal: forgetting a name and recalling it later. Concern: changes that disrupt daily life.", "Movement, sleep, social ties, and managing health support the aging brain.", "These habits genuinely help but are not a certain shield against decline.", "Memory changes that interfere with everyday tasks deserve a doctor's visit." ],
